    "title": "IBD performance regression in 27.0rc1",
    "body": "While investigating the variance in IBD when synchronizing from network nodes and comparing it to synchronizing from a local node, I noticed a significant slowdown when I switched the synchronizing node to 27.0rc1. When connected to a local node (also 27.0rc1), it reaches block 120,000 about 10% slower on average than 26.0, with a much higher variance. I measured around 100 runs of each, alternating between the versions every time. Headers (pre-)sync is not included in the measurement. OS is Windows 10, I'm using pre-built binaries for both versions.\r\n\r\n26.0:\r\n![ibd26](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/assets/43024885/5851cdc2-5f42-41c0-a76a-a70327c66c0d)\r\n\r\n27.0rc1:\r\n![ibd27rc1](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/assets/43024885/0c844086-c080-470a-8d82-42e2678b4c13)\r\n",
